President Donald Trump has announced his intention to nominate James W. Carroll Jr. of Virginia as the Director of the Office of National Drug Control Policy. Carroll currently serves as the Acting Director of the ONDCP and has held various positions in the Trump Administration, including Assistant to the President and Deputy Chief of Staff at the White House, General Counsel of the Office of Management and Budget, and Deputy Assistant and Senior Counsel to the President. He has also worked at the Ford Motor Company and held positions in the George W. Bush Administration.